PROMPT 89: What are the requirements for temporary traffic signals at work zones?
======================================================================
RESPONSE:
- Temporary traffic control signals used to control road user movements through TTC zones and in other TTC situations shall comply with the applicable provisions of Part 4.
- A temporary traffic control signal that is used to control traffic through a one-lane, two-lane section of roadway shall comply with the provisions of Section 4O.02.
- When temporary traffic control signals are used, conflict monitors typical of traditional traffic control signal operations should be used.
- Where pedestrians are detoured to a temporary traffic control signal, an accessible path shall be provided.
- Temporary traffic control signals shall be used in TTC zones such as temporary haul road crossings; temporary one-way operations along a one-lane, two-way highway; temporary one-way operations on bridges, reversible lanes, and intersections.[[SRC_2]]- Temporary traffic control signals (see Section 4D.11) used to control road user movements through TTC zones and in other TTC situations shall comply with the applicable provisions of Part 4.
- A temporary traffic control signal that is used to control traffic through a one-lane, two-lane section of roadway shall comply with the provisions of Section 4O.02.
- When temporary traffic control signals are used, conflict monitors typical of traditional traffic control signal operations should be used.
- Where pedestrians are detoured to a temporary traffic control signal, an accessible path shall be provided.
- Temporary traffic control signals shall be used in TTC zones such as temporary haul road crossings; temporary one-way operations along a one-lane, two-way highway; temporary one-way operations on bridges, reversible lanes, and intersections.[[SRC_2]]

